creator: Hind, Henry Youle, 1823-1908. (author)
description: Hind, Henry Youle: 1823-1908. Born and educated in England; to Canada, 1846; professor of geology and chemistry, University of Toronto, 1853-1864; geologist on Red River exploratory expedition sent out from Canada, 1857; in command of Assiniboine-Saskatchewan exploratory expedition, 1858; later led surveying expeditions to eastern parts of Canada, including Labrador (Wallace, Dictionary of Canadian biography). // Text in double columns. For English versions, see Peel 365 and 367.
